(1, '2019-09-13 07:03:31', '2019-09-14 20:52:34', '0-10V调光电源的工作原理', 'The working principle of 0-10V dimming power supply', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">0-10V调光电源从狭义上讲有0/1-10V调光两种，其实PWM(脉宽调制)信号调光和电阻(电位器)调光从调光操作过程上讲和0/1-10V是一样的，只是调光原理会有所区别。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">此类电源调光平滑、均匀，从调光上来讲，是可控硅调光无法比拟的。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">按应用场合不同，0-10V调光电源分为恒流驱动和恒压驱动电源。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \"><strong>0-10V调光</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">0-10V调光也叫0-10V信号调光，是把0-10V的模拟信号转换成PWM调光信号，是一个模数转化的过程，通过0-10V电压变化,改变电源输出电流,调整亮度。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">此种调光具备开关功能，启亮电压在0.3V。例如:当0-10V调光器调制到0V时,电流降到了0,即灯光亮度处在关闭状态(具备开关作用)；当0-10V调光器调制到最大10V时,输出电流也将达到电源输出电流的100%,灯光亮度也将是100%。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \"><strong>1-10V调光</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">1-10V调光原理与0-10V一致，区别在于1-10V不能将灯具调到最低关闭，启亮电压一般在0.7－0.8V。当1-10V调光器将电压调到最小1V时,改变输出的电流也是10%；调到10V时,输出电流将达到电源输出的100%,灯光亮度也将是100%。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \"><strong>PWM(脉宽调制)信号调光</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">调光原理：通过把电源改成脉冲恒流源，用改变脉冲宽度的方法，就可以改变其亮度。假如脉冲的周期为tpwm，脉冲宽度为ton，那么其占空比D就是ton/tpwm。改变恒流源脉冲的占空比就可以改变LED 的亮度。 PWM调光一般以控制系统或者调光器的形式实现调光。控制系统可以控制多个线路调光,可负载几千(万)W灯,调光器一般控制最大负载在200-300W左右。</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \"><strong>电阻(电位器)调光</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 2em; color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-family: Arial, 微软雅黑, \">此种调光方式是通过改变电路中分压电阻的阻值，从而改变接入控制电路的参数来实现对输出电流的调节，实现对灯光亮度的调节。</p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">In a narrow sense, there are two kinds of 0-10 V dimming power supply. In fact, PWM (pulse width modulation) signal dimming and resistance (potentiometer) dimming are the same as 0-10 V in the process of dimming operation.&nbsp;It&#39;s just that the dimming principle will make a difference.&nbsp;<br/> This kind of power supply dimming smooth, uniform, from the dimming point of view, is the thyristor dimming can not be compared.<br/> According to different applications, 0-10V dimming power supply is divided into constant current drive power supply and constant voltage drive power supply.</span><span style=\"background-color: white; font-family: 微软雅黑, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">0-10V dimming</span></strong><span style=\"background-color: white; font-family: 微软雅黑, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">0-10V dimming is also called 0-10V signal dimming, which converts 0-10V analog signal into PWM dimming signal, which is a process of analog-to-digital conversion. Through the change of 0-10V voltage, the output current of power supply is changed and the brightness is adjusted.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">his kind of dimming has the function of switch, and the turn-on voltage is 0.3V.&nbsp;For example, when the 0-10V dimmer is modulated to 0V, the current is reduced to 0, that is, the brightness of the light is off (with switching function);&nbsp;When the 0-10V dimmer is modulated to a maximum of 10V, the output current will also reach 100% of the output current of the power supply, and the brightness of the light will be 100%.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"background-color: white; font-family: 微软雅黑, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">1-10V dimming</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\"> </span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">The dimming principle of 1 V-10 V is the same as that of 0 -10 V. the difference is that 1 - 10 V can not adjust the lamp to the lowest brightness, and the turn-on voltage is generally 0.7 V to 0.8 V.&nbsp;When the 1 to 10 V dimmer adjusts the voltage to a minimum of 1 V, the output current is also changed to 10%; when the voltage is adjusted to 10 V, the output current will reach 100% of the output of the power supply and the brightness of the light will be 100%.</span><span style=\"background-color: white; font-family: 微软雅黑, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">PWM signal dimming</span></strong></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">Dimming principle: by changing the power supply into a pulse constant current source, the brightness can be changed by changing the pulse width.&nbsp;If the period of the pulse is tpwm, pulse width is ton, then its duty cycle D is ton/tpwm.&nbsp;The brightness of LED can be changed by changing the duty cycle of constant current source pulse.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">PWM dimming is generally realized in the form of control system or dimmer.&nbsp;The control system can control multiple line dimming, can load thousands (ten thousand) W lamps, dimmer generally control the maximum load is about 200 to 300W.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\"><br/></span></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">Resistance (potentiometer) dimming</span></strong></p><p style=\"text-align:left;line-height:22px;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:&#39;微软雅黑&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;;color:black;background:white\">&nbsp; This dimming mode is to change the resistance value of the voltage division resistance in the circuit, so as to change the parameters of the access control cir<a>cuit to realize</a> the adjustment of the output current and the brightness of the light.</span></p><p><br/></p>');

